# Kafka seed 9 class-preserving shrink summary

Goal: preserve the `RecordBatchTooLargeException` / `log.segment.bytes` failure class.

The generic shrinker is failure-preserving, not failure-class-preserving. For seed 9,
unconstrained shrinking can reduce `message.max.bytes` until the failure collapses into
the simpler `RecordTooLargeException` class. That would no longer represent the distinct
log-segment interaction found in the 50-seed sweep.

Therefore, seed 9 was minimized by constructing a class-isolating config target that:

- keeps `message.max.bytes` high enough for the 1.5 MiB record,
- keeps `replica.fetch.max.bytes` high enough for the 1.5 MiB record,
- keeps `log.segment.bytes = 1048576`, below the 1.5 MiB record batch,
- minimizes unrelated Kafka/resource settings to their first choice.

Minimized config target:

  experiments/kafka-cluster-min-log-segment.nix

Validation command:

  python3 -m topotestix.cli orchestrator run kafka-cluster \
    --seed 1 \
    --name kafka-cluster-min-log-segment \
    --project-root . \
    --config-target experiments/kafka-cluster-min-log-segment.nix

Validation log:

  experiments/kafka-cluster-min-log-segment-run.log

Validated run dir:

  .topotestix/runs/20260615-173157-kafka-cluster-seed-1-kafka-cluster-min-log-segment

Observed result:

  FAIL kafka-large-message-on-kafka1
  PASS remaining 10 Kafka properties

Observed exception:

  org.apache.kafka.common.errors.RecordBatchTooLargeException:
  The request included message batch larger than the configured segment size on the server.

Note: an earlier attempt to use command-line choice overrides directly is preserved in:

  experiments/kafka-cluster-shrink-seed-9-choice-override-limitation.log

That attempt exposed a framework limitation: Kafka settings use quoted Nix attribute names
containing dots, while TopoTestix choice paths also use dots as path separators.
